House of Representatives Member representing Sumaila/Takai Federal constituency of Kano state, Hon. Shamsudeen Dambazau has expressed joy over the Supreme Court judgement in favour of Kano State governor, Dr Abdullahi Ganduje. Hon Dambazau further stated that he has never lost faith in the judiciary, having also gotten judgement on his own election victory via the revered temple of justice. In a statement he personally signed, Hon. Dambazau called on party stakeholders in Kano to rally round the governor to ensure that his administration and party delivers on the next level agenda. ” I am greatly delighted over the Supreme Court’s declaration of Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje over as the rightful winner of the 2019 Kano state Governorship election. ” I have never, as a politician, lost faith in the judiciary because my mandate to serve my people was equally validated via the temple of justice, thus reaffirming our firm belief in the judiciary as the hope of the common man. “I salute His Excellency, the governor, our supporters and members for their temperance displayed in the events leading up to this judgement. ” I therefore call on all citizens of Kano state irrespective of political or religious inclination and the State APC stakeholders to come together in support of Governor Ganduje to ensure the success of the government’s Next Level agenda and to democratically entrench the APC in the state” He said.